<p>

<b>ZyLAB</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../574/1875574.xml">
software company</link> which produces <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../276/8276.xml">
digital</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../723/316723.xml">
archive</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../316/12101316.xml">
enterprise search</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../746/454746.xml">
applications</link> such as ZyIMAGE and ZyINDEX. It was founded in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../886/6886.xml">
Chicago</link></village>
 in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../755/34755.xml">
1983</link>, but currently has headquarters in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../594/137594.xml">
Vienna, Virginia</link></village>
 and <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../844/844.xml">
Amsterdam</link></village>
 as well as sales offices throughout the world.</p>
<p>

It was one of the first companies to produce full <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../640/731640.xml">
text retrieval</link> software to run on the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../032/15032.xml">
IBM PC</link> under DOS then Windows; the company is consistently highly rated by IT industry analysts and was placed in the "Leaders" category of the 2007 <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../363/250363.xml">
Gartner</link></company>
 "Magic Quadrant for Information Access Technology" report.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></p>
<p>

ZyLAB's product line is based around ZyIMAGE, their core technology used to scan, OCR, and search paper documents as well as over 370 electronic file formats in over 200 languages.</p>

